         <div type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn" rendition="class:83233 maturity:83213">
           <ab><lb n="1"/>mukha</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus"/>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
 	         <ab>face</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription apparently functioned as indicator of alignment of the face of the element on which it is inscribed with the face of the <foreign>mukhaliṅga</foreign>. See also the identical or analogous labels <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIC00249.xml">C. 249</ref>, <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIC00250.xml">C. 250</ref> and <ref target="DHARMA_INSCIC00251.xml">C. 251</ref>, and on the compostion of the pedestal see <bibl><ptr target="bib:Parmentier1904_02"/></bibl>, who did not, however, mention the presence of such label inscriptions.</p>
         </div>
